<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>3DCG: Angle Animation</title>
    <%= stylesheets('3dcg', 'box2') %>
    <%= scripts('jquery', 'jquery-ui', 'underscore', 'ace/ace', 'source-editor') %>
    <style>
      img.large {
        width: 60%;
      }

      video {
        margin: 10px auto;
      }
    </style>

    <script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
      MathJax.Hub.Config({tex2jax: {inlineMath: [['$','$'], ['\\(','\\)']]}});
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" async src="https://cdn.mathjax.org/mathjax/latest/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS_CHTML"></script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      Angle Animation
    </header>
    <div id="contents">
      <%= overview(mutually_exclusive_with: ['animations/point-animation']) %>
      <section>
        <h1>Implementation</h1>
        <p>
          By default, the scripting language in your ray tracer only
          supports <code>double</code> animations. For this extension,
          you will add support for <code>Angle</code> animations.
        </p>
        <%= source 'example.chai' %>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Find a way to add support for <code>Angle</code> animations.
            If you find out how <code>double</code> animations work,
            it is truly trivial to adapt it to <code>Angle</code>s.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </section>
    </div>
  </body>

  <script>
    function initialize()
    {
      SourceEditor.initialize();
    }

    $( initialize );   
  </script>
</html>
